title: For Sale:  Ruger SP-101 highly customized by KKM Precision
postcontent:
hi, I am selling my Ruger SP-101 revolver. I had it customized a few years ago by KKM Precision out in Carson City, Nevada and they made a great revolver MUCH better. It was new when I sent it and was flawless out of the box but I had them de-horn it (get rid of the sharp edges and de-horn the hammer) so it wouldn't snag on clothing when drawing the weapon out of a holster. I also had them to smooth the (already great) trigger out some and lighten the pull by several pounds. They also did a BEAUTIFUL satin bead blast job on the finish. It came back so nice that I decided not to carry it. I replaced the original grips with Eagle Secret Service checkered grips. I shot two cylinders through it, (they also regulated the sights..it is dead on @ 15 yards with nice, tight groups) & cleaned it thoroughly and put it back into my safe and its been there for a few years....only getting it out on occasion to clean the outside with a silicon cloth. It has been a safe queen. If you notice the pictures, you can hardly even see the turn ring around the cylinder. The speed loader is not included. I have MUCH more in this revolver than I am asking. If you are a revolver aficionado or just love beautiful collectible, one of a kind firearms then dont let this one pass you by!
The ONLY reason that I am selling it is that, although it was a very comfortable carry in a good paddle holster, I probably wont ever carry it again. I only carried it a couple of times in a Galco paddle holster & it is immaculate...better than NEW! I still have the original box, manual and outer cardboard box. These pictures do not do this revolver justice. It is gorgeous with an awesome trigger pull! Thanks for looking

postcontent:
Unfired.  Purchased from Fleet Farm then upgraded with a Midwest Industries Quad rail with UTG covers, fully adjustable iron sights, a forward sling mount and a sling mount on the Six position UTG stock. Comes with 3  - 30 round magazines. 
     Huldra's Adams Arms patented piston system technology will run cleaner, cooler, and longer than any other AR. The piston system parts and the barrel have been treated with our salt nitride meloniting process making them harder than hard chrome.
     The 5.45x39 caliber bullet matches high muzzle velocity with excellent sectional density, resulting in a flat trajectory and good penetration. The standard ball cartridge will penetrate 5mm of steel plate at a distance of 350 meters. The lowered recoil impulse of the 5.45mm cartridge (verses the 7.62x39mm) has a beneficial effect on accuracy. The 5.45x39mm cartridge is an excellent round that offers comparable penetration, accuracy and lethality to anything fielded by NATO. More importantly, 5.45x39 ammunition is less expensive to shoot! It has been designed to handle dirty and corrosive surplus ammunition. The bolt and bolt carrier have been protected by an ion-bond finish. These processes make the parts more corrosive resistant and harder than hard chrome. Now you have the ability to shoot the inexpensive corrosive mil-surplus ammo without the fear of the parts being unduly worn. Also comes with a Wolff Extra Power Hammer Spring to ignite the older hardened primers.
     The melonited corrosive resistant CrMoV (Chrome-Moly-Vanadium) 4150 barrels provides excellent coating uniformity and no tolerance build up in the barrel to create deviation. They have higher lubricity, last longer and are just plain tougher than chrome lining. The barrel chambers are speed polished, reducing resistance on the cartridge entering and exiting the chamber.

title: For Sale:  AR-15 Piston Rifle CMMG MOD4SA
postcontent:
___This weapon by CMMG has a 16 inch barrel with 1:9 twist rifling. Flat top receiver with dust cover, forward-assist and picatinny handguard (no plastic heat shields, wrap that bitch in a rag!). Comes with two CMMG brand 30 round magazines, and YHM brand BUIS. Sling not included. Only around 500 rounds old. Minor scuffs on finish, but in otherwise excellent shape!
___This particular model was from the first batch of these rifles I think, because CMMG has since put out an updated gas plug. It has two positions (two little notches) that you'll have to figure out, because each one works best for a particular ammunition. Screw the plug all the way in during assembly, and back it up to either the first or the second notch. If you're on the wrong setting, it will short cycle your first few rounds on a fresh 30.
___I smoothed out the feed ramps and added a spacer to the buffer spring for more reliable function. The weapon runs smoother than it did out of the factory now after a proper break in and the aforementioned adjustments. This is not amateur work, I used to fix guns in the military.
___As far as the piston system, it doesn't shoot carbon gas all over the moving parts. Most of the fouling deposits in the gas block, gas tube, and the bolt face, much like an AK-47. Very easy to clean after going to the range.
